"{\"uid\": \"news.cgtn.com-news-2024-07-30-Location-of-Olympic-Village-Sustainable-development-in-mind-1vEXjxjg8JG-p.html\", \"text\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. You can change your cookie settings through your browser.  Copied  The Olympic Village is located in the Seine-Saint-Denis district, on which the movie \\\"Banlieue 13\\\" is based. Criminals? Smugglers? Come on, it's not like the movies! The Olympic Village not only provides essential services for the athletes, but is also set to become a model environmentally friendly new community long after the end of the Games.  Click on the video for a 100-second look at how Seine-Saint-Denis is achieving sustainable development well beyond the Games themselves.  (This video is partly produced by AI)  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\"}"